# Product Requirement Document (PRD): UniSphere

## Project: UniSphere - Unified Campus Club & Event Hub
**Version**: 2.0 (Full-Stack Express, Redux, RAG Vector, Caching & Containerization Edition)  
**Status**: Approved & Released  
**Target Release**: Q3 2026  
**Document Owner**: Antigravity AI  

---

## 1. Executive Summary
UniSphere is a full-stack campus engagement platform designed to centralize extracurricular life, simplify event planning, automate attendance verification, and deliver personalized academic guidance. It eliminates the fragmentation of student life by integrating directories, scheduling, ticketing, and diagnostics into a unified dashboard.

This version marks a complete architectural migration from Java Spring Boot to Node.js (TypeScript/Express) on the backend, Zustand to Redux Toolkit on the frontend, and local H2 to dual-mode PostgreSQL/SQLite databases. It introduces advanced integrations, including simulated SMTP email dispatches, Redis caching, Swagger API docs, Cosine-Similarity RAG vector heuristics, and 8 fully functional interactive sliding drawers.

